723090f-b.text:
(1)
Rutherford Place (center of view from right to left), west Aide, south from East 16th, to and including East 15th Streets, showing Friend's Seminary (first two buildings) and Friend's Meeting House (last building of group, on the left), as seen across Stuyvesant Square Park, from Second Ave. The meeting house was erected in 1860 and is
a Quaker place of worship.
December 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

723089f-b.text:
Rutherford Place, west side, north from East 15th across 16th, to 17th Streets, showing on the S.W. and N.W. corners of East 16th Street, respectively, the Friends Seminary and St. Georges P.E. Church. On the extreme right appears a portion of the former Russian Orthodox Greek Catholic Church which is located on the north side of East 17th Street,
between Second and Third Aves.
September 1937.
George D. Chinn.
